name: Shigure Kosaka - HSDK
description:
A Nice Waifu from Shijou Saikyou no Deshi Kennichi.

Works fine with: <lora:KousakaShigureV2:0.7>, kousaka_shigure, ponytail,

I was only able to isolate one outfit:

  • ShigurePinkOutfit (It her typical pink kimono with an under mesh top)

This was supposed to be an easy retrain but instead i had to clean up the dataset. My oldest loras are really showing their age, I am surprised how nice they came out in retrospect.

I have also added the dataset and the tags summary file so people can experiment.

Note stroked though text are for V1

Might be a bit of a failure. I was only able to get her zigzagged eyebrows at high weight .65+and high steps 30+

She looks perfectly fine at .4 weight but she will be missing her characteristic eyebrows.

Got more accurate results with: <lora:Kousaka_Shigure:.65>, Kousaka_Shigure, big_breasts, eyebrows_visible_through_hair

Got better and consistent results but normal eyebrows result with: <lora:Kousaka_Shigure:.45>, Kousaka_Shigure, big_breasts,

Note: eyebrows_visible_through_hair is not a trigger but without it images are less likely to show the zigzag pattern in her eyebrows.

modelVersions.name: v2.0
modelVersions.description: Was supposed to do a small retraining with updated parameters. Turns out my first loras are rougher than i remember beneath the curtain(I am surprised how good they turned out, LORAs can be really forgiving). Ended up deleting mirrored images because it was something i did back then(and then turn on mirror augment). Clean up and upscale some images. And basically completely redo the tagging as the original was made in deepdanbooru instead of WD.
